history.content:
Although I can't speak for ee120, the other 3 are known to be fairly light in coursework. I think you would have to be careful if project deadlines overlap for those classes, in which case you would have to work in overdrive for 1-3 weeks. I think you should go for it but if you can prepare a backup plan just in case, like maybe take a very light decal and if you fail to meet the deadline for a project in one of those classes then you can drop it while maintaining full-time status.

On the other hand, you would run out of "lighter" technicals to take alongside more involved technicals, which may affect your schedule in the future. This is kind of a minor concern, though.
I am taking ee16b, cs70, cs61b this semester and will take 61c in the summer. I feel ok with the workload now. Is it doable to take ee120, cs161, cs188 and cs186 for fall?
history.subject: course load check
